address: 32 Streatham High Rd, London SW16 1DB, United Kingdom
name: Richard Finch
text: We've been here a few times now (over past 3 years) & food is generally very good & very good value (especially for London!). However, the Pizzas USED to be fantastic (especially the fresh home made sour dough base) BUT to our great disappointment, they seemed to have substituted normal cheddar type cheese instead of the proper buffalo mozzarella you used to get. I understand why they've done this (cost of living yada yada yada...) but as Italians we find this totally unacceptable! I need to point out that the option to switch back to 'proper' cheese is available, but only at an eye watering extra £5 per pizza! This almost DOUBLES the price of the pizza!!! Sorry, but I don't call this a fair deal! But I guess we'll have to blame Covid & Putin & global warming & the Chinese spy balloons etc etc etc for all this. For this reason we feel compelled to only award 4 out of 5 stars as everything else seems up to scratch.

address: 32 Streatham High Rd, London SW16 1DB, United Kingdom
name: Matt Smyth
text:
Really attractive and nice looking pizzeria on the high street. Friendly waiter who served us. Unfortunately though, it took an hour to get the pizza - despite the fact that there were only two other tables in the restaurant at the time!  When the pizza finally arrived it was incredibly watery. Not like real Italian pizza. We told the waiter and he replaced it with an equally watery pizza. Clearly the chef doesn’t know how to make pizza with mozzarella.

Overall we were very disappointed!!... I then found out the owners of the restaurant also own the Italian Polish shop on the corner by the station (which is excellent by the way), however, this only fuelled my disappointment as they should know better.

With Pizza Express next door and Adome around the corner they really need to get their s***t together if they are going to compete.

Willing to give it another go, but please, guys, sort it out!!!  It could be amazing. As a Streatham resident we want good places to go to.
title: Italian Bistro (Italian Restaurant)

text:
This was my second time at the restaurant and I can say it wasn't as good as when I went a month ago.
Last time I would have given it a 5 out of 5. This time it's 3 out of 5.
First, I ordered bruscetta as a starter because I loved it last time. Last month I got 3 prices for £2.50. This time I got 1 piece for£3.50!! What??!!
The other disappointing part of the meal was that the pizza was undercooked and wet. Maybe it was a different cook this time, but you could taste the difference.
I see a few of the pizzas have gone up by a pound, but you shouldn't lower the quality of the food to cover it.
I'll give the place one more try (it is the best pizza in town) but if it's bad, I won't be going back.

text: Surprise!  This may be the best meal I've had in my month long stay here!  My fish was excellent, nice and tasty, the potatoes were scrumptious and the spinach was perfectly cooked, all with a nice glass of house wine and a delicious tiramisu to follow for only £20. Can't believe this hands down beat other way pricier meals in some very fancy joints in London. The manager who was working the front of the restaurant was very receptive to suggestions on how to make the place more inviting. A few tweaks and this place could be the go-to place of choice for a romantic or celebratory dinner. Hope they continue to do well and are still here when I next return.

name: John Ditchfield
text:
Very disappointing in just about every respect. Awful service, poor food and an interior which immitates just about every other mid-range Italian..

Our food took about 45 minutes to arrive. The starters were hopeless. I had the bresolla which was served with a huge wedge of cold mozzarella on a bed of undressed rocket.

My wife had some of the limp prawns served with soggy vegetables.

It's the first time I've seen bruscetta served with chunks of cheese. This isn't a good Innovation in my view.

The owner was terribly apologetic and there was clearly an issue with the system for managing orders.

I suspect they can do a rather good pizza as the dough is good although rather salty for our tastes.

address: 32 Streatham High Rd, London SW16 1DB, United Kingdom
name: Danny Salazar
text:
We regreted going into the azzuri instead of pizza express. We opted for "authentic" italian only to be dissapointed. The only good thing about the azzuri is the decor and the fried squid starter.

I had the azzuri lasagna which was an utter shambles. It looked as though they microwaved a slice of lasagna from the morning and topped it off with lots of tomato puree to mask how old it was. The whole thing tasted like marinara sauce from subway.

Moving on to the seafood tagliatele;  the prawns were very rubbery, the mussels was basically just empty shells whilst the only saving grace was the squid.

We didnt even bother to finish eating the mains.  We would have been better of going tescos next door and buying two ready meals instead of the two dreadful mains. To compound the misery  of our evening at the azzuri, my other half started to feel unwell 10 minutes after leaving the establishment.

Overall i think it should just stick to selling pizzas instead of serving dreadful food masked as authentic italian cuisine.
title: Italian Bistro (Italian Restaurant)

name: Nnenna Ngwu
text:
Pretty non descript set up anyway, not the fanciest but nice enough for a quick bite. However we may have had better luck next door at Pizza Express. For all the desire for authenticy... the starters took forever to arrive on a fairly quiet Friday night. There seemed to be just one waitress on... The bruschetta and olive starters are impossible to get wrong anyway and they did not fail there. However the service was much to be desired... a good 20min wait for the starters... even longer for the main.Got fed up waiting for the mains so requested a takeaway box which is taking even longer to appear.

Not impressed unfortunately.

address: 32 Streatham High Rd, London SW16 1DB, United Kingdom
name: Ali Hamoudi
text:
Very poor service went there first time with my friend the juice was in kid glass for£3.50 the food was good. I said I'll give it another try with my family we went there was only one table as I work in the industry I know how good service should be. There was literally no service the server took the order served the food didn't check back didn't offer xtra drinks or desserts the bill arrived with 12.5% service charge for the worse service I got I still paid it .
I just want to say if u guys want to do well u need to train ur staff up to standards.

address: 32 Streatham High Rd, London SW16 1DB, United Kingdom
name: Bhanu Patel
text: NOT WORTH ANY STARTS AT ALL - Atrocious - My daughter and I went there first time on Sunday. It was not busy at all. Being vegetarians we ordered a margarita to share and asked for chillies. The waitress confirmed if it was flakes or fresh chillies. We said fresh chillies but we got flakes, but ignored that. We both had about a quarter pizza left when my daughter notices that there was a piece of ham on her slice. When we called the staff over they had to check that we had indeed ordered a margarita, they would not listen to us. No apologies but told we could have another margarita. We refused and walked out. The manager followed us to the car and asked me to pay for my pizza, but we only had one pizza. He then said I would ask that you do not come back to our restaurant again. Like we would ever go back there!!!!!
